 pleading from serious researchers who feared that Leary was going to &#822=
0;wreak havoc on all of us doing LSD work all over the nation,&#8221; Leary=
 pushed on, like the friend who gets too high and gets everyone in trouble.=
 According to Pollan, Leary said things like &#8220;LSD is more frightening=
 than the bomb,&#8221; and &#8220;The kids who take LSD aren&#8217;t going =
to fight your wars. They&#8217;re not going to join your corporations.&#822=
1;&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The FDA didn&#8217;t like the sound of that, ordering =
in 1966 that researchers halt all work with psychedelics. Neither did Trick=
